						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Except a lot of games use horizontal scrolling with horizontal mirroring, such as <em>Super Mario Bros. 3</em>. That's why I've tried to use the term &quot;vertical arrangement&quot; to represent the $2000/$2800 layout where the nametable is 32 cells wide and 60 cells tall.</div><br />Well H-scroll obviously doesn't mean that the game must scroll horizontally, but that horizontal scrolling takes you into the second nametable instead of mirrored VRAM. I say call it scroll mapping or nametable arrangement, either is fine, but mirroring is just backwards. Although it might be a bit late to change a convention like that.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

